<DocsLayout title="Fade Effect">
  <h1>Fade Effect</h1>
  <p class="lead">Cross-fades between slides using CSS <code>opacity</code>. Slides are stacked on top of each other; the active one fades in while inactive ones fade out. The transition duration is read from the slider's <code>speed</code> option.</p>

  <h2>Import</h2>
  <pre><code>import {"{"} fadeEffect {"}"} from '@andresclua/sliderkit-effects'</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>crossFade</code></td><td><code>boolean</code></td><td><code>true</code></td><td>When <code>false</code>, all slides stay at <code>opacity: 1</code> and only <code>z-index</code> changes — the incoming slide appears instantly on top without a fade.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>On install the plugin:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Positions all slides <code>absolute</code>, stacked at <code>top: 0 / left: 0 / width: 100%</code></li>
    <li>Reads the slider <code>speed</code> option and applies <code>transition: opacity Nms ease</code> to each slide</li>
    <li>Sets the active slide to <code>opacity: 1</code> and all others to <code>opacity: 0</code></li>
    <li>Resets the wrapper <code>transform</code> to <code>translate3d(0,0,0)</code> so the core's translate animation does not interfere</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>CSS class</h2>
  <p>The container receives <code>.c--slider-effect-fade</code> while the plugin is active.</p>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <pre><code>{`import { createSlider } from '@andresclua/sliderkit'
import { fadeEffect } from '@andresclua/sliderkit-effects'
import { arrows } from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'

createSlider('#my-slider', {
  loop: true,
  speed: 400,
  plugins: [
    fadeEffect({ crossFade: true }),
    arrows(),
  ],
})`}</code></pre>

  <p><a href="/demos/effect-fade">View fade effect demo</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
